sub_title: MBA Economics Pantheon Sorbonne University Paris 1
summary: I am a 3rd Year Economics and Business Economics student with Specialisation in International Business and Major in Marketing. I was raised in an international environment, born in Hungary but completed high school in the European School of Brussels but also studied in a French school for 2 consecutive years. I decided to pursue studies in Economics at Maastricht University as it has been a passion of mine since a young age. The dynamics and working of businesses, the evolution of companies, business operations have always amazed me. This multinational environment showed me the importance of speaking many languages, made culturally aware and taught me the importance of international cooperation. Furthermore, I learned how to be part of a group and also how to stand out as a leader and when to step back to follow the others
